#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:97
msgid "Netlifyでの対応"
msgstr "Compatible with Netlify"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:99
msgid ""
"Ryeの公式インストールスクリプトは ``curl | bash`` 形式だが、Netlifyでは ``curl -sSf "
"https://rye.astral.sh/get | bash`` "
"の方式でエラーとなったので、代わりにRyeバイナリをダウンロードして展開する方式を採用した。"
msgstr ""
"Rye's official installation script is in the ``curl | bash`` format, but "
"with Netlify, the ``curl -sSf https://rye.astral.sh/get | bash`` method "
"resulted in an error, so I instead adopted the method of downloading and "
"extracting the Rye binary."

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:125
msgid "トラブルと対策まとめ"
msgstr "Summary of troubles and countermeasures"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:127
msgid "poetry時代の ``pyproject.toml`` が残っているとあると `rye init` が失敗する → 削除する"
msgstr ""
"`rye init` fails if ``pyproject.toml`` from the poetry era remains → delete "
"it"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:128
msgid "``setup.py`` があると `rye init` が失敗する → 一時退避すればOK"
msgstr ""
"`rye init` fails if ``setup.py`` exists → Temporarily save it and it will be"
" OK"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:129
msgid ""
"``pyproject.toml`` に ``requires-python = \">=3.8\"`` があると、Ryeが3.8を使ってしまう →  "
"``\">=3.12\"`` に修正"
msgstr ""
"If ``pyproject.toml`` has ``requires-python = \">=3.8\"``, Rye uses 3.8 → "
"corrected to ``\">=3.12\"``"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:130
msgid ""
"``max-complexity`` の設定が間違っているとRuffでエラー → ``[tool.ruff.lint.mccabe]`` に正しく記載"
msgstr ""
"If the ``max-complexity`` setting is incorrect, an error will occur in Ruff "
"→ Correctly described in ``[tool.ruff.lint.mccabe]``"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:135
msgid "まとめ"
msgstr "summary"

#: ../../../blog/posts/2025-05-31-migrate-poetry-to-rye-netlify.rst:137
msgid ""
"Ryeは開発者体験が非常に良い一方で、NetlifyのようなCI環境での対応には少し工夫が必要だった。 "
"移行はやり切れた。poetryとの違い、性能メリットを感じることもできた。今後はryeを基点にした開発にシフトしノウハウを蓄積したい。"
msgstr ""
"While Rye has a very good developer experience, it needed a bit of work in a"
" CI environment like Netlify. The transition has been completed. I was also "
"able to feel the differences and performance benefits compared to poetry. In"
" the future, we would like to shift to development based on rye and "
"accumulate know-how."

